item.title: CVE-2017-7474|2024-08-05T16:04:11.544Z -- red%20hat%2C%20inc. -- keycloak%20node.js%20adapter
item.description: It was found that the Keycloak Node.js adapter 2.5 - 3.0 did not handle invalid tokens correctly. An attacker could use this flaw to bypass authentication and gain access to restricted information, or to possibly conduct further attacks.
